Functions.answer:
\cite[Example~4.4.6]{SohrabBasicRealAnalysis2}
For $x \in \mathbb{R}$, $\lfloor x \rfloor := \max\{n \in \mathbb{Z} : n \leq x\}$.
Also written $[x]$ (Sohrab) or $\lfloor x \rfloor$ (standard).

\cite[Example~3.2.11]{LeblBasicAnalysis}
$D : \mathbb{R} \to \{0,1\}$ by
\[
  D(x) := \begin{cases} 1 & x \in \mathbb{Q} \\ 0 & x \notin \mathbb{Q}. \end{cases}
\]

\cite[Exercise~4.1.14]{BartleSherbertRealAnalysis4}
$f : \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}$ by
\[
  f(x) := \begin{cases} x & x \in \mathbb{Q} \\ 0 & x \notin \mathbb{Q}. \end{cases}
\]

\cite[Example~3.2.12]{LeblBasicAnalysis}
$T : (0,1) \to \mathbb{R}$ by
\[
  T(x) :=
  \begin{cases}
    1/q & x = p/q \in \mathbb{Q} \text{ in lowest terms, } p,q \in \mathbb{N} \\
    0   & x \notin \mathbb{Q}.
  \end{cases}
\]
Also called the <em>ruler function</em> or <em>popcorn function</em>.

\cite[Problem~23(a)]{SohrabBasicRealAnalysis2}
$f : \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}$ by
\[
  f(x) := \begin{cases} x & x \in \mathbb{Q} \\ -x & x \notin \mathbb{Q}. \end{cases}
\]

\cite[Exercise~4.1.5]{LeblBasicAnalysis}
$f : \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}$ by
\[
  f(x) := \begin{cases} x^2 & x \in \mathbb{Q} \\ 0 & x \notin \mathbb{Q}. \end{cases}
\]

\cite[Example~4.2.12]{LeblBasicAnalysis}
$f : \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}$ by
\[
  f(x) := \begin{cases} x^2 \sin^2(1/x) & x \neq 0 \\ 0 & x = 0. \end{cases}
\]

\cite[§5.2.6]{ThomsonBrucknerBrucknerERA}
Let $K \subseteq [0,1]$ be the Cantor ternary set. The
<em>characteristic function of $K$</em> is $\chi_K : [0,1] \to \{0,1\}$,
\[
  \chi_K(x) := \begin{cases} 1 & x \in K \\ 0 & x \notin K. \end{cases}
\]

